  "novel_contributions": [
    "We gradually \"modernize\" a standard ResNet toward the design of a vision Transformer and identify several key components that contribute to the performance difference.",
    "We propose a family of pure ConvNet models dubbed ConvNeXt, constructed entirely from standard ConvNet modules.",
    "ConvNeXt competes favorably with Transformers in terms of accuracy and scalability, achieving 87.8% ImageNet top-1 accuracy and outperforming Swin Transformers on COCO detection and ADE20K segmentation.",
    "The paper shows that many Transformer architectural choices can be mapped to ConvNet instantiations without introducing attention-based modules.",
    "The paper demonstrates that ConvNeXt retains the simplicity and efficiency of standard ConvNets while scaling well to larger models and larger datasets."
  ],
  "key_claims": [
    {
      "claim": "A standard ConvNet can be modernized using Transformer-inspired design choices to match or exceed hierarchical vision Transformers while remaining purely convolutional.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract; 2. Modernizing a ConvNet: a Roadmap",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "The enhanced training recipe alone raises ResNet-50 performance from 76.1% to 78.8%, showing that training techniques explain a substantial part of the ConvNet/Transformer gap.",
      "evidence_section": "2.1. Training Techniques",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "ConvNeXt-T reaches 82.1% top-1 accuracy on ImageNet-1K and ConvNeXt-B reaches 83.8% at 224^2, outperforming Swin Transformer of similar complexity.",
      "evidence_section": "3.2. Results",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "With ImageNet-22K pre-training, ConvNeXt scales further and ConvNeXt-XL reaches 87.8% top-1 accuracy on ImageNet-1K.",
      "evidence_section": "3.2. Results",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "ConvNeXt achieves on-par or better COCO detection and instance segmentation performance than Swin Transformer, especially for larger ImageNet-22K pre-trained models.",
      "evidence_section": "4. Empirical Evaluation on Downstream Tasks",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "ConvNeXt achieves competitive ADE20K semantic segmentation results with UperNet, including 54.0 mIoU for ConvNeXt-XL with ImageNet-22K pre-training.",
      "evidence_section": "4. Empirical Evaluation on Downstream Tasks",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "ConvNeXt models exhibit strong robustness and domain generalization, outperforming state-of-the-art robust transformer models on several benchmarks.",
      "evidence_section": "B. Robustness Evaluation",
      "page": null
    }
  ]
}